column5: Wow you were right nothing in the sky not even a misquito. But peaceful I might add.  Sorry for lack of action. Would have been nice to see some shots.  dsn
and thats why its called hunting and not shooting...  last night i cooked 2 woodys in the pressure cooker. not as good as roasted but still good
Those pictures and the out come look just like fishing on scugog

Those pictures are exactly why I feel the way I do about both fishing and Hunting... The beauty of what is around us everyday gets missed when our lives are hectic... You captured a beautiful memory.  Too bad about the lack of geese but then there is lots of time left in the season for a couple I am sure.  Cheers,  Jen
Yep Jen, we all need to enjoy (somehow) what we have/do on a day to day basis.  Entropy
I see it as a lack of meat... nice pictures though! being out there is 90% of the experience.
Theres about 15 of them goose poop machines in my back yard...you're welcome to them.
There was about 600++++++ in the cut corn field behind my house last  Sunday evening here in Claremont.  Quite a sight to see when they took off.
